<br>
I would like to thank Pe-Choke Martinez for letting us back into this game, we sure as hell couldn't have done it without you. What do you think of the curse of the bambino now buddy? Thank you Mike Mussina, for keeping us in that game and to the rest of the Yankees for once again proving that never say die attitude and magic still lives within the pinstripes. Thank you Mariano Rivera for being nearly unhittable, going the extra 3-inning distance, and baffling Red Sox hitters once again. Aaron Boone, for showing that even a baseball the hero might turn out to be the most unlikely person. Finally, one big thank you to the Bambino, for watching over us, and assuring those wretched Red Sox still pay for that 85 year old mistake.<br>
<br>
To all you Red Sox fans, I would like to dedicate a song by Kate Bush, though many of you may be more familiar with Maxwell's more recent incarnation. The song is &quot;This Woman's Work&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Pray God you can cope!&quot;<br>
<br>
